# HOUSING CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: housing
scope: housing.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for housing.

## policy_rules
Housing policy constrains:
- who may occupy housing
- who may enter or view housing details
- what placement actions are allowed
- what housing detail may be disclosed
- when housing paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- occupancy eligibility must be explicit
- access eligibility must be explicit
- placement allowance must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public housing summary
- resident-scoped detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical housing detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow housing access only for valid role and scope
- allow placement only for valid authority
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden occupancy claims
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If housing identity,
occupancy scope,
access scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the housing path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- occupancy policy is explicit
- access policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
